MALPHURS v. UNITED STATES. No. 11624. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit April 8, 1947. See also 46 F.Supp. 903. M. H. Myerson, of Jacksonville, Fla., for appellant. Herbert S. Phillips, U. S. Atty., of Tampa, Fla., and Arthur A. Simpson, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Jacksonville, Fla., for ap-pellee.

Before SIBLEY, WALLER, and LEE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The evidence was sufficient to take the case to the jury.

Judgment affirmed.
